The wait time for service is horrible. I’ve went three times and had the same exact experience. I wait 30 minutes before anyone comes to the table to take any drink orders than wait 1hour or more for my food. It has never happened any faster. I did enjoy their fried shrimp and usually the pastelillos are great but today they gave me unflavored shrimp wrapped in dough. I can tell they threw these together after forgetting about my order because it took 1 full hour for this simple appetizer to make it to my table, and this was after me saying something to the staff. This place has potential. The drinks have gotten a lot better. But the service is just truly bad and after today, I can’t say I care much for the food anymore.

Ended up leaving without eating or drinking anything. We went during happy hour hoping to get some cocktails and food. We were the only people at the place which seemed strange, but we decided to give it a try anyways. We sat at the table for about 10 minutes before the waitress even came over. We asked the bus boy what the happy hour specials were and if they had a drink menu, he was sweet but said he didn’t know because he just started working there. When our waitress finally came out, she was extremely rude, we asked what the drink specials were and she gave us two options. When we asked the prices she rolled her eyes at us. We ordered two coladas and some guacamole, after 15 minutes nothing had come out so we decided to leave. Absolutely no reason for such terrible service, especially when we were the only 2 in the place. We wont be back.
